Recently, I did an investigation on my credit report and found several items on there to be inaccurate.

Under 15 U.S. Code 1681e ( b ) Accuracy of report, whenever a consumer reporting agency prepares a consumer report, it shall follow reasonable procedures to ensure the maximum possible accuracy of the information concerning the individual about whom the report relates.

